	<div class="entry" id="entry-6">
					
		<span class="date">June 27, 2005</span>
			<h2><a href="http://blogs.adobe.com/podcast/2005/06/macromedia_podc.html">Macromedia Podcast #1</a></h2>
			<div class="entry-body">
				<p>Welcome to the first <a href="http://weblogs.macromedia.com/podcast/media/mmdrp_6-27-05.mp3">Macromedia Developer Relations Podcast</a>. Below are all the links referenced during the podcast. If we left anything out, let us know by leaving<br />
us a comment.</p>
<ul>
<li><a href="http://www.andersblog.com/">Mark Anders Weblog</a></li>
<li><a href="http://weblogs.macromedia.com/flashjavascript/">The Flash / JavaScript Integration Kit</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.communitymx.com/content/article.cfm?cid=D7491&amp;print=true">Using<br />
the Macromedia Flash / JavaScript Integration Kit</a> (Danny Patterson)</li>
<li><a href="http://weblogs.macromedia.com/mxna/flashservices/">The MXNA Flash Services</a></li>
<li><a href="http://richardleggett.co.uk/blog/index.php/2005/06/23/mxna_flash_lite_app">Richard<br />
Leggett&#8217;s MXNA Flash Lite Application</a></li>
<li><a href="http://weblog.infoworld.com/udell/2005/06/01.html">Web-friendly<br />
rich Internet apps, continued</a> (Jon Udell) </li>
<li><a href="http://weblogs.macromedia.com/cantrell/archives/2005/06/deep_linking_in.cfm">Deep<br />
Linking in Flash and AJAX Applications</a> (Christian Cantrell) </li>
</ul>
<p>You can download the podcast from <a href="http://weblogs.macromedia.com/podcast/media/mmdrp_6-27-05.mp3">here</a>.</p>
